<p style="margin: 0px;">
An internship is more than a summer job — it’s a great way to explore a career in financial services. You'll work alongside full-time associates as part of a team, developing the personal and professional skills that can give you a major advantage in the workplace.
</p>

<H2 class="p"><span class="bd"><b>Intern Program Requirements</b></span></H2>
<ul>
	<li>Overall GPA of 3.0 or above</li>
	<li>Full-time undergraduate or graduate student attending an accredited college/university</li>
	<li>Non-graduating status (i.e. graduation date cannot be prior to August of any given year)</li>
	<li>Eligible to work 40 hours per week for the program length of 10-12 weeks</li>
	<li>Business or technical-related majors</li>
	<li>Must possess the right to work in the United States, as it is not the practice of Bank of America to sponsor individuals for work visas.</li>
</ul>

<H2 class="p"><span class="bd"><b>Application Process</b></span></H2>
<p style="margin: 12px 0px 6px 0px;">
To apply for one of our summer internships, please visit our Undergraduate/Analyst and Graduate/Associate websites to view the different opportunities available. Click the send us your resume link, sign in as a new or returning user and designate your program(s) of interest. We recruit for our summer internship opportunities through mid-February.
</p>

<H2 class="p"><span class="bd"><b>What interns do</b></span></H2>
<ul>
	<li>Interns generally work forty hours per week for ten to twelve weeks, in a supportive learning environment supporting the day-to-day operations of a project or department.</li>
	<li>Internship positions mirror the positions of full-time Bank of America associates.</li>
</ul>

<H2 class="p"><span class="bd"><b>Internship benefits</b></span></H2>
<ul>
	<li><span class="bd">Compensation.</span> Compensation for our internship positions is competitive. Other benefits include access to Associate Banking and two paid days off if the intern works more than 10 weeks. Interns are classified as temporary associates for benefits purposes.</li>
	<li><span class="bd">Networking.</span> Interns have the opportunity to meet and interact with senior executives at a variety of meetings and receptions. In addition, volunteer and social activities are offered for networking with peers.</li>
	<li><span class="bd">Professional development.</span> Your work will be measurable and realistic, and allow you to stretch your ability. To give you practice interacting with managers and demonstrating your business acumen, you'll present a summary of your project work to managers and peers at the end of your internship.</li>
	<li><span class="bd">Guidance.</span> At the beginning of the summer, managers assist interns in developing a performance plan to establish goals and objectives. These plans are reviewed during the intern's end-of-summer performance evaluation. In addition, interns are paired with a mentor for further guidance during their summer experience.</li>
</ul>

<H2 class="p"><span class="bd"><b>Dates</b></span></H2>
<p style="margin: 12px 0px 6px 0px;">
The Intern Program typically begins in May and continues through September. Our application deadline is mid-February each year. We usually fill positions by mid-April.
</p>

